post_text: Information about 21st Century Distance Learning Summer School!!
shared_text:
Cave Springs School 21st Century Community Learning Center
May 28 at 4:22 PM ·

Cave Springs School's 21st Century Summer School will be starting on Monday, June 1st. This year we will have to continue with distance learning during summer school.

We will be passing out packets of fun activities and books to our students throughout the month of June using our normal school bus routes.

We will have the enrollment forms for summer school on Monday with our school lunch deliveries at our regular lunch delivery stops. Please make sure you fill one out so that we know who wants to be involved and then we will start running regular school bus routes so that each child may receive a packet at their home.

So keep an eye out for your bus drivers and you might also see a teacher or two on the bus!

We're very excited for all the fun we will be passing out to all the kiddos! We will have more information coming soon, so keep an eye out and like this page!

shared_text:
Jennifer Crumby
May 22 at 12:06 PM ·

ATTENTION parents of 10th graders: If your student is or was in the 10th grade during the 2019-20 school year and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application BASED ON YOUR 2020 ESTIMATED INCOME.

The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020, deadline.

After you complete your 2020 taxes next year, you will then be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal tax return to verify that your 2020 income was under $55,000. OK's Promise will hold your application as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu

It’s time to fill out your 2020 Census! Here’s how:

Go to the website: my2020Census.gov.
Click on the button that says “Start Questionnaire”
Don’t have access to the internet or a smart phone or need assistance in another language? Call (844) 330-2020. It’s easy and safe.
No Census ID? No problem! Everyone can fill out the Census right now.

If you don’t have a Census ID, you can choose “If you do not have a Census ID, click here.” It will ask you to fill out some basic information, like your address, and then you can get started!

Fill out your 2020 Census today at my2020census.gov. When everyone counts, everyone wins!

post_text:
Cave Springs High School will join other HS nationwide on Friday to honor the 2020 Senior Class!

High schools around Oklahoma and across the country are banding together to honor the 2020 senior class amidst the coronavirus pandemic.

On Friday, April 10, at 8:20 p.m., Hornet Field and outdoor stadiums around the state and country will turn on their lights for 20 minutes to show their appreciation for the senior class as part of the “Be the Light” campaign.

The lights are a beacon to show the Senior Class we are thinking of them and to remind them there will be a time where we will be all together once again.

The “Be the Light” campaign has been spreading across the nation as schools look for a way to celebrate their graduating seniors who are having their final memories in high school stripped away due to the Covid-19 virus.

Take a drive by the field during that time and honk to show your support. Please remember to adhere to social distancing protocol and stay in your vehicle.

Why the exact time?
20:20 for 20 minutes for the Class of 2020!

post_text:
A great educational resource for home!

Beginning Monday, March 30, OETA will be adjusting its daytime schedule to provide curriculum-based programming for students Monday through Friday from 6 a.m. until 6 p.m. which will last until the end of the school year . Most importantly, OETA World is being repurposed to include educational programming during these times.

Teachers and parents are encouraged to visit www.OETA.tv/LearningAtHome to view an updated program schedule, OETA’s statewide channel list, curriculum and activities. Every show on OETA World, for the foreseeable future, is linked PBS LearningMedia, which provides videos and interactives, as well as audio, documents, and in-depth lesson plans. Additionally, most programming on PBS Kids is already free and viewable at PBSkids.org and using the PBS Kids app.

As you know, the State Department has extended our Spring Break until April 6th.

We will be providing Grab & Go breakfast and lunches for our students. They will be available for pickup from 10:00 am to 12:00 pm, Monday through Friday. The student must be in the vehicle to receive the meals. Please pull up by the awning in front of the elementary building and it will be brought out to you. Please do not try to come into the buildings. We are working with the State Dept. to try and deliver some of the meals, we will post any updates as soon as we get them.

There will be a special State School Board Meeting on March 25th to discuss the next steps that will be taken.

Teachers: Mr. Brown has sent out emails with the information he has been given, and will be sending out more info as he receives it. Please read the emails and let him know if you have any questions.

Truancy court has been moved to April 28th at 3:30 p.m.

Some personnel will be at school, but due to the safety of our staff we ask that you call with any questions you have.

Mr. Brown made a special announcement announcement yesterday by one call, this is the message he sent out.

“Special announcement with a response to student dress code. Students of Cave Springs school are expected to dressed appropriately for attendance at school. Students’ appearance and behavior should not distract classmates from the important task of learning. Students may not wear revealing clothing, male or female. Shorts should be no shorter than mid thigh and no low-cut tops. We are going to enforce this policy, and parents may be called to come and get your child. So I would suggest that before your child leaves the house that you check and make sure that they're dressed appropriately. If you have any questions don't hesitate to call me at school 918-775-2364 my extension is 102 thank you have a good weekend.”

7th grade parents:

Our school is required by law to make sure every 7th grade student has taken the TDAP vaccine.

If your 7th grader has not taken this shot please do so by Friday, August 23. After this date, your child will not be allowed to return to school until we have received updated shot records showing they have received their TDAP shot.

Monday, Aug. 5th is the First Day of School! Please make sure you send your enrollment forms back with the kids. Class starts at 8:00 a.m., and buses will run at regular times.

Tuesday, Aug. 6th the High School will be having physicals. Make sure you get a physical form and get it sent back to school.

Can’t wait to see all those smiling faces Monday morning!!

post_text:
Just a little information about this page, before the new school year starts.

This page is voluntarily ran by two teachers, with administration’s permission. This page is here to help connect parents, students, and the community with what is happening at our school. We try our best to answer any questions that you have, but this is not always possible. We would like to keep this page going, but we want it to be a positive place to post information about our school! We are asking that you please be respectful with your comments and direct messages.

If there is an issue or a complaint about something that happens at school, on the bus, etc. please contact administration because there is nothing we can do about it through this page.

Let’s have a great school year!

Thank you,
Teresa Buzzard
